## My honest view

This is a strong idea, but it only works if the pet is tied to **meaningful educational effort**.

If it is just decoration, users will ignore it.
If it is too gamey, it will distract.
If it is too punitive, it will backfire.

The sweet spot is:

**gentle companion + visible progress + effort-based reward + shared identity across apps**

That could work very well for the sort of apps you are building.

